            680,
            106
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Motivations ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            117,
            143,
            189,
            170
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "VectorMapNet ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            443,
            142,
            532,
            173
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Qualitative Results ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            779,
            143,
            894,
            170
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Autonomous driving systems require an understanding of map elements on the road,including lanes,pedestrian crossing,and traffic signs,to navigate around the world. ",
        "bbox": [
            18,
            184,
            285,
            216
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "LIDAR Pairwise $\\textcircled{8}$ Involves a complex pipeline   \nscans alignment Globallyonsistentpointcloud Static HD map   \nIMU $\\textcircled{2}$ Costly and labor intensive Manual Annotation $\\textcircled{8}$ Needs timely update   \nodometry ",
        "bbox": [
            24,
            233,
            275,
            335
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In contrast, we focus on using onboard sensors, including LiDARs and cameras,to estimate map elementson-the-fly. ",
        "bbox": [
            20,
            346,
            270,
            377
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Contributions ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            112,
            523,
            196,
            551
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "·VectorMapNet isanend-to-end mappingapproach.   \n·We utilize polyline to accommodate the heterogeneous nature of map elements. Our method achieves promising performance in online semantic HD map learning tasks. ",
        "bbox": [
            20,
            567,
            258,
            631
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "image",
        "img_path": "/data/huangyc/Document2All/posterDataOutput_vlm/VectorMapNet: End-to-end Vectorized HD Map Learning_poster/auto/images/images/fig_1.jpg",
        "image_caption": [
