            637
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "image",
        "img_path": "/data/huangyc/Document2All/posterDataOutput_vlm/VectorMapNet: End-to-end Vectorized HD Map Learning_poster/auto/images/images/fig_3.jpg",
        "image_caption": [
            "Using polylines as primitives has brought us two benefits compared with baselines: "
        ],
        "image_footnote": [],
        "bbox": [
            692,
            189,
            985,
            521
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "·Polylines effectivelyencode the detailed mapgeometries,e.g.,the cornersof boundaries (red elipses). ",
        "bbox": [
            697,
            557,
            972,
            575
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Polyline representations prevent Modelfrom generating ambiguous results,as it consistently encodes direction information.Incontrast,Rasterized methodsare prone to falsely generating loopy curves (blue ellipses ). ",
        "bbox": [
            696,
            579,
            975,
            624
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Problem Formulation ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            89,
            648,
            220,
            676
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Quantitative Results ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            531,
            644,
            655,
            672
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Centerline Generation ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            845,
            644,
            982,
            674
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Similarto HDMapNet,our task is to generate vectorized mapelements usingdata from onboard sensors of autonomous vehicle,such as RGB cameras and/or LiDARs.These map elements include: ",
        "bbox": [
            21,
            687,
            277,
            718
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "·Lane dividers:boundaries dividing lanes on the road,usuallystraight lines.   \nRoad boundaries:boundaries of roads separating roads and sidewalks,typically irregularly-shaped curves of arbitrary lengths. Pedestrian crossings:regions with white markings indicating legal pedestrian crossing points, typically represented aspolygons.   \nCenterlines:line segments that commonly used for driving direction,vehicle positioning,and navigation. ",
        "bbox": [
            22,
            723,
            285,
            848
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Why use polyline to represent maps? ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            41,
            861,
            265,
            891
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Using polylines to represent map elements has three main advantages: ",
        "bbox": [
            23,
            904,
            207,
            920
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "·Polylinesarea flexible primitive that can represent complex geometric elements in HD maps.   \n·The order of polyline vertices isa natural way to encode the direction of map elements.   \n·The polyline representation has been widely used by downstream tasks,such as motion forecasting. ",
        "bbox": [
            20,
            925,
            288,
            972
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Top-right Middle Start . Top-most Right-most Bottom-left End Lett.ostBottom-most Polyline Bounding Box SME Extreme Points ",
        "bbox": [
            302,
            655,
            501,
            708
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Three different keypoint representationsare proposed here. ",
        "bbox": [
            304,
            712,
            460,
            727
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "VectorMapNet for Motion Forecasting ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            308,
            763,
            491,
            786
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Toevaluate the capacity of our method and to investigate its usefulness in downstream tasks,we put our predicted HD map to the test within a motion forecasting task. ",
        "bbox": [
            298,
            806,
            496,
            853
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Wereporttheaverage precision thatuses Chamferdistanceand Fréchet Distanceas the threshold. ",
        "bbox": [
            508,
            686,
            676,
            716
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Motion Forecasting heavily relies on precise map information for accurate prediction of future motion. ",
        "bbox": [
            299,
            861,
            475,
            890
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
